          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 1. Ge(Li)- spectrometer with a crystal size of",
                "100 cm*3 and the energy resolution of 3.8 keV for",
                "Eg=661 keV was used for check measurements.",
                "2. Ge(Li)- spectrometer with a crystal size of 80 cm*3",
                "and the energy resolution of 2.8 keV for Eg=1.332 MeV",
                "was used for the final series of measurements."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "48-CD-114",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.99
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The targets were self-supporting",
                "foils of Cd  (3.3 and 5.9 mg/cm2 thickness)with 99%",
                "enrichment of 114Cd.",
                "As a monitor target a copper foil with the natural",
                "isotope composition (4.05 and 4.18 mu-g/cm2 thickness)",
                "located at the place of main target was used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Cross sections were defined by induced",
                "activity method. 1. The check measurements allowed to",
                "establish the presence of the gamma-lines under study",
                " (190, 558, and 725 keV) in the 114In decay spectrum",
                "and to estimate their relative intensity.",
                " 2. Final measurements were carried out 48 h after the",
                "exposure (run 1) and 42 days after the exposure (run 2)",
                "They were helped to solve problems arising from",
                "short-lived isotopes 113In, 115In, and 116In",
                "and annihilation peaks."
              ]
            }
          ],
